# Refactor: Move Page Endpoints to /pages

## Status

- not-started

## Goal

Move all custom page-related API endpoints from /pages/_ to top-level /pages/_ for clarity and RESTful convention. Update backend handler, routes, and document migration steps. Ensure all frontend and integration points are updated accordingly.

## Steps

1. Update backend/internal/page/handler.go to mount all page endpoints under /pages instead of /pages.
2. Update any references in backend/internal/page/service.go, repository.go, and interface.go if route paths are hardcoded or referenced.
3. Update frontend API calls and route references (src/hooks/usePageData.ts, src/pages/custom-pages/CustomPages.tsx, etc.) to use /pages/\*.
4. Update documentation in backend/README.md and .specs/landing_page_spec if route paths are mentioned.
5. Test all page CRUD, browse, engagement, and admin endpoints for correct behavior and permissions.
6. Announce the change in .todo/.tip and notify frontend/backend contributors.

## Notes

- Keep config-only endpoints (e.g., landing page config, factory reset) under /config if not user-facing.
- Ensure WebSocket events and permission checks are unaffected.
- See /memories/repo/skaia_exploration.md for current endpoint mapping and frontend usage.
